{
  "plugins": {
    "posthtml-include": {
      "root": "./src"
    },
    "posthtml-expressions": {
      "root": "./src/partials",
      "locals": {
        "top": [],
        "body": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "<a name=\"select\">In the</a> following map, explore how summertime temperatures affect neighborhoods of different HOLC grades in various cities and decades. When you scroll into the map, a layers interface appears. You can toggle HOLC boundaries. You can also toggle the visibility of impervious surfaces, as well as the visibility of two categories of imperviousness."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "When any impervious surface is visible, the color legend becomes a bivariate matrix of colors. Clicking on any square in the legend filters the map to show only HOLC areas with that color."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "The final research document is available <a href=\"https://jsonkao.github.io/redlining-heat/Final.pdf\">here</a>."
          },
          {
            "type": "graphic",
            "value": {
              "asset": "map.html"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "The temperature distribution in <span class=\"variable-city\"></span> by HOLC grade is visualized in the density plot below."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "<img class=\"chart\" id=\"chart\" />"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "After running Tukey’s Test at a 95% confidence interval for <span class=\"variable-city\"></span>, we can observe in both years which HOLC grades’ neighborhoods were significantly cooler or hotter than neighborhoods in other grades."
          },
          {
            "type": "html",
            "value": "<img class=\"chart chart-tky\" id=\"chart-tky\" />"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "<a href=\"#select\">Go back up</a> to view the map."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "<hr/>"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Nationwide, the distribution of temperatures for each HOLC grade shows that formerly redlined neighborhoods experience hotter summers, both in 2000 and 2020. Applying Tukey’s Honestly Significant Differences Test at a 95% confidence interval gets us the results below."
          },
          {
            "type": "html",
            "value": "<img class=\"chart chart-tky\" id=\"nation-chart-tky\" />"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "The individual per-polygon temperature means are shown in the following density plot."
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "<img class=\"chart\" id=\"nation-chart\" />"
          }
        ],
        "headline": "Redlining’s Legacy in Heat Inequality:  Exploratory Page",
        "date": "April 26, 2021",
        "byline": "Jason Kao",
        "footer": "Code to reproduce data and visualizations is on <a href=\"https://github.com/jsonkao/redlining-heat\">GitHub</a>.",
        "USE_NEWS_NAV": true,
        "USE_EYE_NAV": false,
        "USE_COVER_HED": false,
        "IS_EMBED": false,
        "DOC_URL": "https://docs.google.com/document/d/1W8mgGgVzw98WqZy8MBZQ_2IcCHyBtZh7uTZjAIDLKOc/edit"
      }
    }
  }
